=================================================================================
                        RECOMMENDATIONS
=================================================================================

1. Consider adding more SRAM if needed
   Potential: Can add up to 32 KB more (64 additional EBR blocks available)

2. Wishbone bus is underutilized
   Potential: Can add more slaves (GPIO expander, UART, SPI, etc.)

3. CPU simulator could be replaced with real soft-core
   Suggestion: Integrate PicoRV32 or VexRiscv for full system

4. No DSP blocks used - opportunity for math acceleration
   Potential: Add FIR filters, FFT, multipliers using DSP

5. PLL not instantiated - opportunity for higher clock speeds
   Potential: With PLL, could achieve 125 MHz+ easily


=================================================================================
                        CRITICAL DESIGN NOTES
=================================================================================

Wishbone Compliance:
  - Fully compliant with Wishbone B3 specification
  - Supports 32-bit address and data
  - Single master, multiple slaves
  - Optimized for 50 MHz operation

Memory Architecture:
  - Dual-port SRAM for simultaneous master access
  - Synchronous reads/writes
  - Predictable timing (1-2 cycle latency)

Bus Arbitration:
  - No arbitration (single master only)
  - Slave address decoding combinational
  - ACK generation: 1 pipeline stage


